<section id="fb1">
	<p align="left">1. When you give your name to someone this is an introduction.</p>
</section>
<section id="fb2">
	<p align="left">2. This is important so that the Examiner can check the candidate's identity.</p>
</section>
<section id="fb3">
	<p align="left">3. Identification is essential, you can't take the exam without it.</p>
</section>
<section id="fb4">
	<p align="left">4. The Examiner asks all the questions.</p>
</section>
<section id="fb5">
	<p align="left">5. This is one of the first questions the Examiner will ask.</p>
</section>
<section id="fb6">
	<p align="left">6. The Examiner gives her name without the candidate having to ask. </p>
</section>
<section id="fb7">
	<p align="left">7. She doesn't have to go into lots of detail but gives a short description.</p>
